\id JAS - Akawaio New Testament Translation Project 
\h ISENS 
\toc1 Enno'sa' Kareta Isens Winɨpaino 
\toc2 Isens 
\toc3 Isens 
\mt2 Enno'sa' Kareta 
\mt1 Isens 
\mt2 Winɨpaino 
\imt1 Ekamanin 
\ip \bk Enno'sa' Kareta Isens Winɨpaino\bk* esi iku'to' pe auro'kan nɨto' amʉranʉ'sa' menukasa', “12 kaisaron kon iko' amʉ' tʉpataron kon koro'tawɨrɨ iye'ta'nʉ'sa' kon enakan.” Imenukanin uya kɨpo'po'nan kuru rɨ main ekamanin apurɨsa' auro'kan nɨto' enpoikanin pe iku'to' pe auro'kan nɨto' pɨ', pu'ketʉ pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Kʉri'san pe e'nɨto' eseru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ato'. Kʉri'san pe e'nɨto' winɨ ɨ'si'taino pɨ' isauro'sa' se warai'nan pɨ', imaminke' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨ'rɨ pʉra rɨ entu'ma' rɨ e'nɨto' pɨ', ɨri uya mo'kan nɨto', wakʉ pe ato', ɨsewaruma'ke' pe, apurɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikupʉ, ani apurɨto', pu'ketʉ, ɨsipɨ' e'nɨ, mɨ pe e'ku'nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨ pe te'ku'sen pe pʉra e'nɨto', tʉron kon eseru aimenka, utapurɨn nɨto' tʉuseta'kai' pʉra e'nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpʉreman nɨto' pɨ' isauro'sa'. 
\ip Enno'sa' kareta uya kuru anʉnpɨtʉ usennakan pe pʉra ikupʉ esi apurɨto' pokon pe, Kʉri'san pe e'nɨto' ekareei yau. 
\iot Iyawon Ekamanin 
\io1 Ekamanin (1:1) 
\io1 Apurɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pu'ketʉ (1:2-8) 
\io1 Ɨ'rɨ pʉra entu'ma' e'nɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mamin (1:9-11) 
\io1 I'tun mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'tupɨ'nɨto' (1:12-18) 
\io1 Eta mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikupʉ (1:19-27) 
\io1 Panaman tenu yawon ke e'nɨ namai' (2:1-13) 
\io1 Apurɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itʉrawasooi (2:14-26) 
\io1 Kʉri'san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyani (3:1-18) 
\io1 Kʉri'san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non (4:1—5:16) 
\io1 Iu'matʉ pe ɨ'si'taino tu'kan ku'to' pɨ' rɨ auro'kan nɨto' (5:7-20) 
\c 1  
\p  
\v 1 Isens, Papa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Itepuru Sises Kʉrai poitorʉ winɨpaino,\x - \xo 1:1 \xt Ma'siu 13:55; Ma' 6:3; Inkupʉ'pʉ 15:13; Kare'siya 1:19\x* 
\p 12 kaisaron kon iko' amʉ' tʉpataron kon koro'tawɨrɨ iye'ta'nʉ'sa' kon enakan: Miyarɨ'nokon. 
\s1 I'tun Nɨto' Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ I'tupɨ' Nɨto' 
\p  
\v 2 Utonpa ton, pori' pe kuru e'tɨ', tu'kan nɨ ɨ'si'taino ton i'tupɨ'nɨto' uye'sa' a'tai ɨpona'nokon,  
\v 3 apʉne pʉra i'tu auya'nokon apurɨto' auya'nokon i'tupɨ'to' uya iyannawɨrɨ utɨn nɨto' kupʉ.  
\v 4 Entakato' tʉtʉrawasooi i'ma'kai, iyakʉ'pʉsa' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyenuka'sa' pe ɨwesi kon pa, ɨ'rɨ i'se pʉra rɨ.  
\v 5 Ipu'ketʉ pʉra ɨtonpa kon esi yau, Papa pɨ' nekama'poi, itʉnin amʉre' pe pʉra esii'ma tanporon kon ena', irepa iya rɨ mɨrɨ, ipɨ' tʉusakorotai' pʉra.  
\v 6 E'tane apurɨi'ma nekama'poi ikasimai'ma pʉra, apʉne pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ ikasimai'ma ekama'ponin esi mɨrɨ sipa'sipa parau po, pese'tɨ nʉposi'manʉ nʉpininpanʉ kasa.  
\v 7 Kʉrɨ rɨ ka'pon kʉ'senuminkanin ɨ'rɨ eporo tʉuya Itepuru winɨpai tukai';  
\v 8 ikasimanin pe kuru iyesi mɨrɨ, inkupʉnʉ esi mɨrɨ petenan pe pʉra. 
\p  
\v 9 Entu'manin akon wannɨ ne'kupʉi mɨ pe eke yau tesi pɨ'.  
\v 10 E'tane imaminke' ne'kupʉi mɨ pe aiko pe tenasa' pɨ', apʉne pʉra wana' ipʉrʉ uma'ta kasa ima'tato' oton.  
\v 11 Apʉne pʉra wʉi enu uyepʉ punin ta'netʉ a'kɨrɨ, mɨrɨ uya ite' seketanʉkʉ; itipʉrʉ uta'mo'ka, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itakorʉwanooi uma'ta. Mɨrɨ kasa imaminke' uma'ta tʉtʉrawasooi kupʉ iya koro'tau.\x - \xo 1:11 \xt Aisaya 40:6-7 (LXX)\x* 
\p  
\v 12 Pori' kʉrɨ rɨ ka'pon ti'tupɨ'to' entakanin, uko'man nɨto' arʉkooi, kʉron tato' epoto' iya oton, Papa nekama'pʉ kamoro ti'nʉnkanin nan pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 13 “Papa uya i'tupɨ'nɨto' ya' utʉsa',” kʉ'kanin ɨnʉ' rɨ i'tupɨ'nɨto' ya' te'tʉsa' a'tai, apʉne pʉra Papa esi i'tupɨ'nin pen ɨri ke, ɨnʉ' rɨ i'tupɨ'nin pen kʉrɨ rɨ;  
\v 14 e'tane ka'pon e'tʉrʉ i'tupɨ'nɨto' ya' ɨri i'se iye'to' winɨ, mɨrɨ uya rɨ ipi'sikʉ mɨrɨpan epori'ma ɨri pɨ'.  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ a'tai si, ɨri i'se te'sen entusa' a'tai, ɨri ton eseru ku'nin pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ si mɨrɨ ɨri ton eseru usemo'kasa' a'tai, uma'tan nɨto' ya' arɨ iya. 
\p  
\v 16 Kɨsenku'tɨtʉu, utonpa ton nʉ'kwɨ.  
\v 17 Tanporon wakʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipan nɨ wakʉ ton repan nɨto' esi ka'tawinɨ tʉuye'sen ka' a'kwarii Kʉipʉnʉ winɨpai, tʉusensimasen pen a'kwarʉ'pʉ usensimapɨtʉ kasa.  
\v 18 Teseru poro ne'nɨsa' iya i'napairon main awɨrɨ, tanporo wapiyaro' kon inkapʉ'san imunkɨ amʉ' pe\f + \fr 1:18 \fq wapiyaro' kon inkapʉ'san imunkɨ amʉ' pe; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq imunkɨ amʉ' pe kuru rɨ\ft —Kiri' nʉmenuka'pʉ uya, \fq wapiyaro' kon inkapʉ'san \ft ta. Main, Mosi' winon uya enupan ɨ'rɨ amʉ' ɨmʉrewato' ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kiyari akʉ'pʉsa' anʉmʉ e'sara'tɨ esi Papa iwano' pe kuru rɨ, mɨrɨpan esi itenawon pe kuru tasa'.\f* usen nɨto' kon pe inkapʉ'san koro'tau. 
\s1 Eta Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Iku'nin Pe E'nɨto' 
\p  
\v 19 Utonpa ton nʉ'kwɨ, mɨrɨ wenai i'tutɨ': Tɨwɨ tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' nesii inke pʉra etanin nan pe, tɨnɨn pɨ' tʉusauro'san pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨnɨn pɨ' tʉusakorotasan pe,  
\v 20 ka'pon sakorooi uya Papa e'to' i'se ipokena' pe uko'man nɨto' nepʉ pʉra iyesi.  
\v 21 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ɨri eseru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri inonkatɨ' eke pe ɨwoi'nokon na'ne', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨ pe te'ku'se pʉra Papa Maimu anʉntɨ' ɨyewan kon ya', iye'pɨnka'sa' na'ne' ayau'nokon; main ɨpika'tɨnin kon pe kuru te'sen. 
\p  
\v 22 Wakʉ main awɨrɨ e'tɨ', etanin pe rɨken pʉra. Mɨrɨ a'tai, ɨiwano' kon pe ɨusenku'tɨ kon pen.  
\v 23 Ɨnʉ' rɨ esi a'tai main etanin pe e'tane iku'nin pe pʉra, kʉrɨ rɨ esi mɨrɨ ka'pon, wanamari ya' temʉ' ennin kasa,  
\v 24 mɨrɨpan utɨ tʉusene'pʉ tʉpo, inke pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ kasa tesi tukai' tʉusene'pʉ pu'tɨka'nʉkʉ iya.  
\v 25 E'tane kʉrɨ ipoi rɨ tenu tʉtʉse wakʉ main, mo'kanin wannɨ ennin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuko'mansen serɨ kupʉ pɨ' tʉneta'pʉ tʉpu'tɨka'nʉ'se pʉra e'tane ikupʉ pɨ'—kʉrɨ rɨ uya wakʉ epoto' oton mɨrɨ tʉnkupʉnʉ yau. 
\p  
\v 26 Ɨnʉ' rɨ ka'pon esi yau Papa pokon pe tʉuko'mansen pe te'ku'sen pe tani mainanpai'ma pʉra, kʉrɨ rɨ usenku'tɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa pokon pe iko'manto' napurɨnʉ esi notʉn pe rɨ.  
\v 27 Wakʉ kuru esukenan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imaku'pɨ pʉn Papa pokon pe uko'man nɨto', Papa, ukʉipʉnʉ kon e'to' i'se esi se kasa: piyapaino kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itaan'pʉ ima'tasa' kon tʉmainanpai' to' usewankamato' yapai, ɨri serɨ non eseru uya tʉma'tanʉ'to' apai nɨrɨ te'mainanpa pe. 
\c 2  
\s1 Tenu Yawon Ke E'nɨ Namai'no 
\p  
\v 1 Utonpa ton, a'kwa yawon Uyepuru kon Sises Kʉrai apurɨnin pe ɨwesi kon koro'tau, tenu yawon ke ke'tʉu.  
\v 2 Ka'pon uyepʉ pe iyesi yau ayamʉrasa' kon koro'ta', korʉ pun konekasa' irimuui pe, wakʉ ya' iyepontɨpɨ'sa', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ entu'manin, ɨri rɨ nin ipon nɨrɨ uyepʉ.  
\v 3 Kʉrɨ kuru wakʉ pe iyepontɨpɨ'sa' kupʉ auya a'tai wakʉ pe, “Se kuru wakʉ ayapon,” tai'ma ipɨ', entu'manin pɨ', “Mɨ airɨ e'soto'ka',” mɨrɨ pe pʉra, “Ereuta' non po u'ta piyau,” tai'ma. Mɨrɨ ku'sa' auya'nokon a'tai,  
\v 4 iye'menkasa' kon pe pʉra pe' me'ku'atʉu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eseru aimenkanin pe ɨyenasa' kon, ipoken pʉra ɨri pe ɨusenuminka kon winɨ rɨ? 
\p  
\v 5 Etatɨ', utonpa ton nʉ'kwɨ: Papa uya pe' kamoro pata enu yau entu'manin nan pe te'san anʉnsa' pʉra nai apurɨto' yau eke pe to' e'to' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ, esa' wannɨ pe te'to' anʉnnin pe ti'nʉnkanin nan e'to' pe?  
\v 6 E'tane entu'manin nan sapemasa' auya'nokon. Imaminke' ton pen pe' kamoro ɨkota'manin kon? Kamoro pen pe' kamoro ko'tʉ ta' ɨpi'si'nin kon?  
\v 7 Kamoro pen pe' kamoro eke ipɨ' ɨye'tʉsa' kon na'ne' ese' sapema pe tʉusauro'san pen? 
\p  
\v 8 Eke, Itepuru maimu iye'menukasa' na'ne' itekare yau yawɨrɨ kuru ɨwesi kon yau, “Ɨtonpa i'nʉnkakɨ, mɨsi'nʉnkayai'ne' kasa,”\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Ripaiti'kas 19:18\f* tawon, ipoken ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ.  
\v 9 E'tane tenu yawon ke ɨwesi kon yau, aumakoita kon; Main, Mosi' winon uya nin si ama'tanʉkʉ kon mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ Main i'kwɨ'nin pe ɨwesi kon pɨ'.  
\v 10 Apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ tanporo Main yawɨrɨ na'ne' e'tane rɨ ita'mo'ka tikin nan yau rɨ esi mɨrɨ ɨri pe, tanporo rɨ i'kwɨ'sa' iya pe.  
\v 11 Apʉne pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ, “Iyemari'masa' kʉsekumankai,”\f + \fr 2:11 \ft E'sotas 20:14; Isu'taronomi 5:18\f* tawon uya rɨ marɨ, “Ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉ'wɨnɨi,”\f + \fr 2:11 \ft E'sotas 20:13; Isu'taronomi 5:17\f* tasa' esi. Iyemari'masa' ekumankanin pe pʉra rɨ ɨwesi yau, e'tane iwɨsa' auya yau, main i'kwɨ'nin pe rɨ ɨyenasa' mɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 12 Asauro'tɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iku'tɨ', kamo Main, mo'kanin wannɨ yai, iteseru aimenkato' naimenkaton kon pe,  
\v 13 apʉne pʉra Papa uya eseru aimenka usenpoikato' oton usentu'man pe pʉra kʉrɨ isentu'masa' rʉ'pʉ pen pona. Usentu'man uya eseru aimenka wapiya'ka mɨrɨ! 
\s1 Tapurɨsen Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Tʉku'sen 
\p  
\v 14 Wakʉ pe pe' iyesi, utonpa ton, ka'pon e'kupʉ yau apurɨto' esa' pe e'tane ɨ'rɨ rɨ kupʉi'ma pʉra? Mɨrɨ warai pe' apurɨto' uya ipika'tɨ?  
\v 15 Utonpa kon, warawo' mɨrɨ pe pʉra uri'san esi yau ipon pʉra, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉi kaisa rɨ inanʉmʉnʉ iti'kiyari pʉra,  
\v 16 ɨtonpa kon uya ta pe iyesi yau ipɨ', “Enta, wakʉ pe e'kɨ ukayai' ɨpɨ'; ikomi' pe pʉra ɨko'mankɨ, wakʉ pe mata're'tɨi',” e'tane ɨ'rɨ kupʉi'ma pʉra rɨ i'se iye'to' pɨ', wakʉ pe pe' iyesi?  
\v 17 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ, apurɨto' esi, ikupʉ uya isakonʉ'tɨ pʉra iyesi yau, iyeri'sa' pe rɨ iyesi. 
\p  
\v 18 E'tane tʉron nɨ uya ta poken iyesi, “Apurɨto' esa' pe ɨwesi; iku'to' esa' pe esi,” ta. 
\p E'tane ta uya nin, “Anapurɨnʉ ikupʉi'ma pʉra enpoikakɨ uyena', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ unapurɨnʉ ikupʉi'ma enpoikato' pe uya ɨyena',” tasa'.  
\v 19 Apurɨ auya moron tikin nan nɨ Papa. Oso! Mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ apurɨnin nan kamoro ɨri a'kwarʉ ton, ɨsi'nʉkʉi'ma ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 20 Iya'kwarʉ pʉnon ɨmɨrɨ'nokon! Ɨni'tupai pe' me'atʉu apurɨto' ikupʉi'ma pʉra e'nɨ esi notʉn pe?\f + \fr 2:20 \fq notʉn pe; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq iyeri'sa' pe\f* 
\v 21 Utamokori kon pe' Epʉra'an pɨ' ipokena' e' ta'pʉ pen pe' inkupʉ'pʉ wenai Aisi' tʉmu tʉsa' iya a'tai, Papa ena' use'man nɨto' apon po?\x - \xo 2:21 \xt Iseneses 22:1-14\x* 
\v 22 Ene auya'nokon inapurɨnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inkupʉnʉ e'tʉrawasoma'pʉ ɨsi'kaisa rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inkupʉnʉ uya nin si inapurɨnʉ enuka'nʉ'sa' mɨrɨ.  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itekare iye'menukasa' nin si uta'ku'tɨsa', “Epʉra'an uya Papa apurɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨ pɨ' nin si ipokena' pe te'sen ta,”\f + \fr 2:23 \ft Iseneses 15:6; 2 Kʉrono'kʉrʉs 20:7; Aisaya 41:8.\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa tonpa tukai' esa'sa' na'ne'.  
\v 24 Ene auya'nokon ka'pon koneka Papa uya wakʉ pe inkupʉnʉ winɨ, inapurɨnʉ winɨ rɨken pen. 
\p  
\v 25 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ, Reyapu, ekumanpɨ' te'sen pɨ' ipokena' e' ta'pʉ inkupʉ'pʉ wenai, ama'ai non ense'na itɨsa' kon apontɨsa' iya a'tai, mɨrɨpan kon ennoko'pʉ iya tʉron nɨ awɨrɨ pɨ' pen pe'?\x - \xo 2:25 \xt Isa'suwa 2:1-21\x* 
\v 26 Pun, iya'kwarʉ pʉn esi iyeri'sa' pe kasa, apurɨto' tʉku'sen a'kɨrɨ pʉra esi iyeri'sa' pe rɨ. 
\c 3  
\s1 Ani, Tenupansen Pen Nɨ 
\p  
\v 1 Utonpa ton, ti'sa amʉ' pe esi i'se ke'tʉu, apʉne pʉra urɨ'nokon enupanin nan pe te'san eseru aimenkato' oton mɨrɨ ipan pe ɨsɨ pe.  
\v 2 Tanporo tu'kan yau rɨ tʉuta'mo'kasan urɨ'nokon. Ɨnʉ' rɨ esi yau ipoken pʉra te'sen pe pʉra tʉusaurokʉ yau, wakʉ pe kuru iyesi mɨrɨ, tʉpun nɨ si esa' pe iyesi. 
\p  
\v 3 Kaware mʉta ya' itewa pʉ'kʉ tʉsa' a'tai, umaimu kon awɨrɨ iye'to' pe, tanporo rɨ kaware ra'tɨ mɨrɨ.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ pe pʉra eke kanau amʉ' pɨ' i'tutɨ'. Eke ton pe rɨ iye'tane, pana'pan nɨ a'setun narɨnʉ pe, aiko rɨ e'se'tɨnin uya e'se'tɨ, anin e'to' i'se awɨrɨ itɨto' pe.  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ kasa si ani aiko rɨ pun pʉ'kʉ esi, e'tane eke pe tʉutapurɨsen. Ɨsenuminkatɨ' eke rɨ yu' epo'tɨ pɨ' aiko rɨ apo' e'sirinkasa' ke.  
\v 6 Ani rɨ marɨ esi apo' pe, eke pe rɨ ɨri yen pe rɨ iyesi upun kon pʉ'kʉ pe. Tanporo rɨ ka'pon a'si'sa' iya, iko'manto' eseru rɨ epo'tɨto' pe ikupʉ iya, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyepo'tɨ rɨ apo', ekota'man pata'se' yau. 
\p  
\v 7 Tanporon kon nɨ o' amʉ', toron amʉ', ene amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ parau kawon kon nɨ ene amʉ', moro' amʉ' rɨ esi tenupansan pe, mɨrɨpan kon nɨ enupankasa' ka'pon uya,  
\v 8 e'tane ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ani enupanka pʉra iyesi. Tereutasen pen nɨ ɨri pe kuru rɨ iyesi, eke pe rɨ eri'nʉ'kanin paisin yen pe iyesi. 
\p  
\v 9 Ani ke uyepuru kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ukʉipʉnʉ kon apurɨpɨtʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨrɨ ke rɨ ka'pon amʉ' pa'nʉkʉ, Papa waraino kon pe ika'sa' kon.\x - \xo 3:9 \xt Iseneses 1:26\x* 
\v 10 Mɨrɨ rɨ mʉta apai apurɨpɨ'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ e'pa'nʉ'nɨto' epa'ka. Utonpa ton, serɨ kʉse'ku'nin!  
\v 11 Asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ pe' wakʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ine'ne'\f + \fr 3:11 \fq ine'ne', \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq i'ne', \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq ɨsɨ. \ft (Apʉne, v. 12 nɨrɨ enka'kɨ.)\f* tuna epa'ka poken nai mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ tuna epa'kato' euta yai?  
\v 12 Utonpa ton, pi' e' pe' epeta poken nai are' pe, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kʉre' e' pe' epeta poken nai pi' pe? Ine'ne' pe tepa'kasen tuna uya wakʉ enpa'ka pen nɨ nɨrɨ. 
\s1 Asa'ron Tʉponaron Ipu'ketʉ 
\p  
\v 13 Ɨnʉ' nai pu'kena' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ito'ka'nʉ'nin ɨ'koro'tau'nokon? Tɨwɨ nenpoikai wakʉ pe tʉuko'manto' eseru ke, mɨ pe te'ku'se pʉra tʉnkupʉnʉ ke ipu'ketʉ winɨpai tʉuye'sen.  
\v 14 E'tane ɨsɨ pe ɨyɨkɨntato' kon, amʉre' pe ɨwe'to' kon esi yau ɨyewan kon yau, ipɨ' katapurɨtʉu, mɨrɨ pe pʉra i'napairon pɨ' kasi kʉkatʉu.  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ waraino rɨ ipu'ketʉ u'tɨ pʉra iyesi Epʉn poi, e'tane non winon nɨ, iya'kwarʉ pen nɨ, Makoi winon nɨ.  
\v 16 Ɨkɨntan nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ amʉre' pe e'pai e'nɨto' yau, ɨsiporo pʉra e'nɨto', tanporon nɨ ɨri rɨ ku'to' eporo mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ yau. 
\p  
\v 17 E'tane ipu'ketʉ, Epʉn poi tʉuye'sen esi mɨrɨ wapiya kuru esukenan nɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto', tʉusi'nʉnkasen, tʉron kon ennin, main awɨron nɨ, ɨsentu'kena' rɨ, eke rɨ wakʉ ku'nin, te'menkasen pen nɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napairon nɨ.  
\v 18 Tʉusewankamai' te'san i'nɨ'panʉ'pɨ'nin nan, usewankaman nɨto' yau pʉra te'pɨnsan uya ipoken e'nɨto' akʉ'pʉsa' anʉmʉ. 
\c 4  
\s1 Papa Ena' E'nonkatɨ' 
\p  
\v 1 Ɨ'rɨ uya epanta'man ɨsipɨ' e'nɨ emapu'tɨ ɨ'koro'tau'nokon? Ipan pe i'se ɨwe'to' kon ayau'nokon na'ne' usewa'noman pɨ' yapai pe' iyepʉ pen mɨ?  
\v 2 Ɨ'rɨ rɨ i'se ɨwesi kon e'tane eporo auya'nokon pʉra iyesi. Iwenai ɨye'wɨnɨ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨ'rɨ rɨ enkuui pe ɨwesi kon, e'tane i'se ɨwe'to' kon eporo auya'nokon poken pʉra iyesi. Ɨsipɨ' ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨyepanta'ma kon. Eporo auya'nokon pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra Papa pɨ' ekama'po auya'nokon pʉra iyesi pɨ'.  
\v 3 Ekama'po auya'nokon a'tai, eporo auya'nokon pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra ɨri pe iteseru esii'ma ekama'po auya'nokon, ɨneporo'pʉ kon ma'tanʉkʉ ke ipan pe i'se ɨwe'to' kon nɨ kupʉ pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 4 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon temari'masa' kon e'tane tekumasan waraino kon ka'pon amʉ', i'tu auya'nokon pʉra pe' iyesi, orʉ kupʉ auya'nokon ɨtonpa kon pe a'tai, Papa ewaruma'tɨ auya'nokon pe iyesi? Ɨnʉ' rɨ orʉ tonpa pe e'paino ena mɨrɨ Papa eyaton pe.  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨusenuminka kon nɨ katɨ iye'menukasa' Papa Maimu uya ta iwenai pʉra rɨ, “Iya'kwarʉ uyau'nokon iko'manto' pe inkupʉ'pʉ esi tiwano' pe rɨken ui'se'nokon,”\f + \fr 4:5 \fq Iya'kwarʉ uyau'nokon iko'manto' pe inkupʉ'pʉ esi tiwano' pe rɨken ui'se'nokon; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Papa esi ita'kwarʉ uyau'nokon iko'manto' pe tʉnkaa'pʉ i'se tiwano' pe rɨken.\f* tukai'?  
\v 6 E'tane eke pe miyarɨ parɨ wakʉ nonkasa' iya upona'nokon. Mɨrɨ pɨ', iye'menukasa' Papa Maimu uya ta, 
\q1 “Papa uya mɨ pe te'ku'sen ewaruma'tɨ, 
\q2 e'tane mɨ pe te'ku'sen pen pona wakʉ nonkasa' tʉrʉ iya,”\f + \fr 4:6 \ft Ipu'ketʉ 3:34 (LXX)\f* 
\m ta iya. 
\p  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ pɨ' si, Papa ena' e'nonkatɨ'. Makoi iwa'kʉ'tɨ', mɨrɨpan ainʉnto' pe ɨpiyapai'nokon.  
\v 8 A'ko pe Papa piya' ɨsi'tɨ', a'ko pe ɨpiya'nokon iye'to' pe. Ɨyemiyatʉ kon ikumi'tɨ', tʉmakooikena' nan ka'pon amʉ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨyewan kon ikorʉkatɨ', ikasimanin ye' ton kuru.  
\v 9 Aya'kwarʉ kon tainʉnpai' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuta'kwarʉpɨ'se, tʉukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'se akarantɨ'. Auta'kɨrɨto' kon ensimatɨ' tʉuta'kwarʉpɨ'se ukaran nɨ pe, pori' pe ɨwe'to' kon ipan pe ɨusewankono'ma kon pe.  
\v 10 Mɨ pe te'ku'sen pe pʉra enatɨ' Itepuru rau, ayanʉnto' kon pe iya. 
\p  
\v 11 Utonpa ton, ɨtonpa kon pɨ' ɨri pe isapema pe tʉusauro'se pʉra e'tɨ'. Ɨnʉ' rɨ ɨri pe isapema pe tʉtonpa pɨ' tʉusauro'sen, mɨrɨ pe pʉra iteseru aimenkanin usaurokʉ main, Mosi' winon pɨ' ɨri pe isapema pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iteseru aimenka iya. Main eseru aimenka auya a'tai, iyawɨrɨ ɨwesi pen mɨrɨ, e'tane iteseru aimenkato' auya po ɨyereuta.  
\v 12 Moro tikin nan nɨken Main tʉnin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iteseru aimenkanin esi, kʉrɨ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ tʉmeruntɨrʉ kenan ipika'tɨto' ike mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ima'tanʉ'to' ike. E'tane si ɨmɨrɨ—ɨnʉ' pe ɨwesi ɨtonpa eseru aimenka pa? 
\s1 Awanapairon Pɨ' Utapurɨn 
\p  
\v 13 Apʉne etatɨ', ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, “Serɨ pe, mɨrɨ pe pʉra awanapai rɨ se pata, mɨrɨ pe pʉra mɨ pata ya' utɨn mɨrɨ, tikin nɨ wʉipiya enno'se'na mɨrɨ yau, pʉrata epoto' kupʉ pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pʉrata eporo pɨ',” tawon nan kon.  
\v 14 I'tu auya'nokon pʉra rɨ iyesi ɨ'rɨ e'kupʉ awanapai rɨ tukai'. Ɨ'rɨ mɨ ɨuko'manto' kon? Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon esi kapuru' pe, aka'ne' pe rɨ tʉusenpoikasen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tapasen kasa.\x - \xo 4:14 \xt Ipu'ketʉ 27:1\x* 
\v 15 E'tane ru'ku, “Itepuru eseru pe iyesi yau, se, mɨrɨ pe pʉra mɨ kupʉ pɨ', uko'man nɨ'nokon mɨrɨ,” tato' auya'nokon pe iyesi.  
\v 16 Na'ne' nin esi, mɨ pe ɨye'kupʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ autapurɨ kon. Tanporo serɨ waraino utapurɨn esi ɨri pe.  
\v 17 Ɨnʉ' rɨ, wakʉ tʉnkupʉnʉ i'tunin, ikupʉ iya pʉra na'ne' umakoita mɨrɨ. 
\c 5  
\s1 Imaminke' Ton Panamato' 
\p  
\v 1 Apʉne etatɨ', ɨmɨrɨ'nokon imaminke' ton, akarantɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'se akarantɨ', apʉne pʉra usewankaman nɨto' uye'nɨ pɨ' man ɨpona'nokon.  
\v 2 Ɨimamin kon a'motasa' man, ene amʉ' uya ɨpon kon ɨ'sa' man.  
\v 3 Ɨkorʉʉi kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsirʉpaai kon ukaranpɨ'sa' man. Serɨ ikaranpɨ'sa' uya apa'nʉkʉ kon mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpun kon anɨ iya apo' kasa. Eke pe kuru ɨimamin kon amʉranʉ'sa' auya'nokon serɨ iweyu ton u'matʉ yau.\x - \xo 5:3 \xt Ma'siu 6:19\x* 
\v 4 Entɨ'! Amainarʉ kon yau iye'tʉrawasomasa' kon epe'pʉ, to' e'ma'pʉ auya'nokon pʉra na'ne' ike ukaran nɨ pɨ' man apa'nʉkʉ kon pe. Ɨi'kiyari kon akʉ'pʉsa' anʉnnin nʉ'san ukaramʉ uya Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye' Itepuru pana eposa' man.\x - \xo 5:4 \xt Isu'taronomi 24:14-15\x* 
\v 5 Ɨuko'mansa' kon man serɨ non po eke pe rɨ ɨimamin kon tepose, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipan pe i'se ɨwe'to' kon kupʉ pɨ'. Ɨyeka'pɨ'sa' kon ɨwɨnɨ kon weyu a'taino pe.\f + \fr 5:5 \fq ɨwɨnɨ kon weyu a'taino pe; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq enta'nan weyu a'taino kasa.\f* 
\v 6 Ɨri ku'nin nʉ'san pen nɨ eno'ma'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉ'ka'pʉ auya'nokon, ɨyewa'nomanin kon pokena' nan pen nɨ. 
\s1 Tʉuseta'kai' Pʉra E'nɨto' 
\p  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ pɨ' si, tʉuseta'kai' pʉra e'tɨ', utonpa ton, Itepuru uyepʉ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ. Apʉne temaina'tɨsen entɨ': tenuri'sen non uya epe'kena' kiyari epetanʉkʉ enupɨkɨrɨ, tʉuseta'kai' pʉra te'sen tuna e'sara'tɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tuna iu'matʉ yawon enupɨkɨrɨ.  
\v 8 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon nɨrɨ tʉuseta'kai' pʉra e'tɨ', pana' pe e'soto'katɨ', apʉne pʉra a'ko pe Itepuru uye'to' man.  
\v 9 Ɨtonpa kon pɨ' te'naipɨ'se pʉra, utonpa ton, ɨyeseru kon kuru nin aimenka mɨrɨ. Eseru aimenkanin man mʉra'ta nau rɨ iye'soto'kasa'! 
\p  
\v 10 Utonpa ton, tʉuseta'kai' pʉra e'nɨto' ento' ipɨ' ɨsɨ moronka a'taino pe, pu'kena' amʉ' entɨ', isauro'sa' kon Itepuru ese' yau.  
\v 11 Mi'tuyatʉi'ne' kasa rɨ, ipʉremasa' pe to' esi ta, kamoro imoronkanin nʉ'san pɨ'. Isopu uya imoronkasa' rʉ'pʉ etasa' auya'nokon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iu'matʉ pe ene'pʉ Itepuru nʉkupʉ'pʉ rʉ'pʉ. Itepuru esi eke pe tʉusentu'masen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aiko tawon nɨ.\x - \xo 5:11 \xt Isopu 1:21-22; 2:10; Eren 103:8\x* 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ entai kuru, utonpa ton, ɨnku'ton kon pɨ' ausaurokʉ kon a'tai Epʉn kʉsesa'tʉu, mɨrɨ pe pʉra non nɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨ'rɨ rɨ. Tɨwɨ, “Ewai',” tato' auya'nokon nesii, ewai' pe rɨ; “Kane,” tato' auya'nokon nesii, kane pe rɨ, ɨyeno'ma kon kuru nin mɨrɨ.\x - \xo 5:12 \xt Ma'siu 5:34-37\x* 
\s1 Apurɨto' Yau Ɨpʉreman Nɨto' 
\p  
\v 13 Ɨtonpa kon nɨ na'kɨ nai ekamʉn yau? Tɨwɨ nɨpʉremai. Ɨnʉ' rɨ pe' nai pori' pe? Tɨwɨ apurɨpɨ'to' eremu yai nʉserenkai.  
\v 14 Ɨtonpa kon nɨ na'kɨ nai takuru'ke? Tɨwɨ so'si epuru ton kɨ'mai tʉpona to' ɨpʉremato' pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉkarapaimato' pe Itepuru ese' yau.\x - \xo 5:14 \xt Ma' 6:13\x* 
\v 15 Apurɨto' yau iyɨpʉremasa' uya takuru'kenan epi'tɨ mɨrɨ; Itepuru uya rɨ i'mʉ'sa'ka. Imakoitasa' pe iyesi yau, ipɨ' rɨ usentu'man.  
\v 16 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ɨtonpa kon pɨ' rɨ amakooi kon ekamatɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨtonpa kon pona rɨ ɨpʉrematɨ', ɨusepi'tɨ kon pa. Ipokena' e' pe te'sen ka'pon ɨpʉrema esi mɨrɨ ipan pe meruntɨ pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉwotori'pɨ ke. 
\p  
\v 17 Iraisa esi'pʉ ka'pon uwarai'nokon nɨ. Iyɨpʉrema'pʉ tʉuta'kwarʉpɨ'se, tuna uyepʉ pʉra iye'to' pe, tuna uyepʉ pʉra si iyesi'pʉ non amankanin pe osorʉwawon pona a'sa'mʉyai wʉipiya airɨ rɨ.\x - \xo 5:17 \xt 1 Kin Amʉ' 17:1; 18:1\x* 
\v 18 Iyɨpʉremakaa'pʉ kanan, mɨrɨ a'tai ka' awonsi'kɨ si tuna uyee'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ si non uya kiyari epetanʉkʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 5:18 \xt 1 Kin Amʉ' 18:42-45\x* 
\v 19 Utonpa ton, tikin nɨ rɨ ɨtonpa kon utano'ma pe iyesi yau i'napairon apai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron nɨ uya ina'po,  
\v 20 se nesii ɨyenu kon yau: Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ tʉmakooikenan na'po ipokenan pen apai uya ipika'tɨ mɨrɨ ima'tato' apai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tu'kan nɨ makooi nɨpontɨ iya mɨrɨ.\x - \xo 5:20 \xt Ipu'ketʉ 10:13; 1 Pi'ta 4:8\x*